data.title: Running a project with --player --project from VS2015 pops up 3D Module License error
data.body:
To reproduce:
-Pull latest from master
-Run CMake_VS2015.bat
-Open Atomic.sln in VS2015
-Set AtomicEditor as Startup Project and set it's Debugging Command Arguments to --player --project "path/to/AtomicExamples/CharacterAnimation3D"
-Debug the solution.

Expected: 
-The player process runs normally

Actual:
-The player process runs with a "3D Module License Required" popup
